Diagnosis.
Atheta pasadenae
can be recognized by the following combination of characters: pronotal hypomera invisible in lateral view, pronotal setation along midline directed anteriad, posterior margin of male tergite 8 quadri-dentate with median emargination wider than the two lateral emarginations (Fig. 3 in
Tronquet 2000
), spermatheca with distal part of distinct shape (Figs. 5–6 in
Tronquet 2000
), internal sac of the aedeagus with a pair of C-shaped lateral sclerites (Figs. 10–11 in
Tronquet 2000
), antennomeres 5–10 transverse.
